b'UIC ranked among top 10 \xe2\x80\x98Best Value\xe2\x80\x99 universities'
b'\n\t\t\t\tSeptember 6, 2018\t\t\t'
b''
b'UIC is ranked among the top 10 \xe2\x80\x9cBest Values,\xe2\x80\x9d according to the Wall Street Journal and Times Higher Education rankings. Photo: Jenny Fontaine'
b'The University of Illinois at Chicago is ranked No. 7 on the \xe2\x80\x9cBest Values\xe2\x80\x9d list \xe2\x80\x94 just behind Harvard University \xe2\x80\x94 in this year\xe2\x80\x99s Wall Street Journal and Times Higher Education rankings.'
b'Wall Street Journal and Times Higher Education rankings'
b'UIC also is ranked No. 29 among more than 400 U.S. public universities, according to the 2019 ranking.'
b'For the first time, the rankings have further analyzed the top 250 universities to create a \xe2\x80\x9cBest Values\xe2\x80\x9d list, which considers overall ranking, tuition, fees, housing, and federal and institutional aid. UIC was listed as No. 7 \xe2\x80\x94 ahead of Georgia Institute of Technology, Rutgers and Stanford in the top 10 list.'
b'The WSJ/THE overall rankings are based on 15 factors across four categories: student outcomes, resources, engagement and environment. Also considered were more than 200,000 student survey responses on topics such as the difficulty of classes, ease of collaboration with classmates, application of course material to the real world, and more.'
